#: ../../source/2fa.rst:2
msgid "Two-Factor Authentication"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:4
msgid ""
"Each user can enable the `two-factor authentication "
"<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two_factor_authentication>`__. After a "
"successful login, a one-time code (6 characters) is asked to the user to "
"allow access to Kanboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:9
msgid ""
"This code has to be provided by a compatible software generally installed"
" on your smartphone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:12
msgid ""
"Kanboard use the `Time-based One-time Password Algorithm "
"<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-based_One-time_Password_Algorithm>`__ "
"defined in the `RFC 6238 <http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6238>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:16
msgid ""
"There are many software compatible with the standard TOTP system. For "
"example, you can use these free and open source applications:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:19
msgid ""
"`Google Authenticator <https://github.com/google/google-"
"authenticator/>`__ (Android, iOS, Blackberry)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:22
msgid "`FreeOTP <https://fedorahosted.org/freeotp/>`__ (Android, iOS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:23
msgid ""
"`OATH Toolkit <http://www.nongnu.org/oath-toolkit/>`__ (Command line "
"utility on Unix/Linux)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:26
msgid ""
"This system can work offline and you don't necessarily need to have a "
"mobile phone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:30
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:32
msgid "Go to your user profile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:33
msgid "On the left, click on **Two factor authentication** and check the box"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:34
msgid "A secret key is generated for you"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:39
msgid "2FA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:41
msgid ""
"You have to save the secret key in your TOTP software. If you use a "
"smartphone, the easiest solution is to scan the QR code with FreeOTP or "
"Google Authenticator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:44
msgid "Each time you will open a new session, a new code will be asked"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:45
msgid "Don't forget to test your device before closing your session"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/2fa.rst:47
msgid "A new secret key is generated each time you enable/disable this feature."
msgstr ""

